 Ngqamakhwe - Ngqamakhwe police arrested a 58-year-old woman for dealing in dagga. "The suspect was arrested on Wednesday, at about 16h00, at Ndende Locality, Mbiza Village, Ngqamakhwe," said police spokesperson, Captain Jackson Manatha. "The suspect will appear before the Ngqamakhwe Magistrate’s Court on Thursday. "She faces a charge of dealing in dagga." Follow more RNEWS articles, subscribe to our YouTube channel and for breaking news LIKE us on Facebook. For news on the Western Cape click here. For great savings on life’s little pleasures visit Bargain Buys!  Know somebody who is getting married, Wedding and Function can assist.  Have kids, then you need to visit Kids Connection. Enjoy food and travel, then visit Home Food and Travel. Need assistance with an online presence, visit Agency One. 